The article discusses Vice President Mike Pence's remarks at the White House regarding President Donald Trump's efforts to rebuild American infrastructure. Pence highlights Trump's dedication to fulfilling his promises to the American people, including job creation, deregulation, and energy independence. Pence also mentions Trump's commitment to repealing and replacing Obamacare. The Vice President emphasizes that American businesses are growing and investing in the country, and unemployment is at a 16-year low. Pence praises Trump as a builder and announces that the President will take historic steps to rebuild America, focusing on infrastructure such as roads, bridges, tunnels, and airports. Pence believes that this action will encourage investment, commerce, and enhance the safety and precision of air travel in the United States. Pence concludes by expressing gratitude for Trump's leadership and determination to restore opportunity and prosperity to the nation.